HEADWORD: Internuncial
<hw>In`ter*nun"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Internuncio</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to an internuncio.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Communicating or transmitting
impressions between different parts of the body; -- said of the nervous
system.</def> <rj><au>Carpenter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Internunciess</ent>⟦br⟧
